This looks much better. You’re now storing state and sending `code_verifier`, so the remaining 400 is likely one of these two things:

## Most likely issue

Your token request is using:

```java
String tokenUrl = "http://keycloak.ns-keycloak/realms/arthur-local/protocol/openid-connect/token";
```

But in `/start` you discovered metadata from:

```java
appConfig.getIssuerUri()
```

and used that to build the authorize URL.

Those two should come from the **same source**. Do not hardcode `tokenUrl`. Use OIDC discovery metadata again in callback.

### Change this

```java
String tokenUrl = "http://keycloak.ns-keycloak/realms/arthur-local/protocol/openid-connect/token";
```

### To this

```java
OidcMetadata metadata = oidcDiscoveryClient.loadMetadata(appConfig.getIssuerUri());
String tokenUrl = metadata.getTokenEndpoint();
```

That avoids subtle mismatches between issuer, realm, and token endpoint.

