## Why I think this is the remaining problem

Your `/start` method is well-shaped now:

* gets app config
* loads OIDC metadata
* generates state/nonce/verifier
* saves transaction
* builds authorize URL

So the callback should mirror that by:

* loading transaction
* loading app config
* loading OIDC metadata
* using discovered token endpoint

That matches your architecture where Arthur Core orchestrates auth and Lancelot supplies app config. 

